examples: a question to which we have only partial answers

adjective.description: Favoring one side in a dispute above the other; biased.
examples: the paper gave a distorted and very partial view of the situation
you know I'm partial to bacon and eggs

noun.description: A component of a musical sound; an overtone or harmonic.
examples: the upper partials of the string

origin: Late Middle English (in partial (sense 2 of the adjective)): from Old French parcial ( partial (sense 2 of the adjective)), French partiel ( partial (sense 1 of the adjective)), from late Latin partialis, from pars, part- part.
